19. requos abhorret a meis moribus: a course which would be (is) in- consistent with my character. Perhaps Cicero means to imply that he is too merciful, that if the question were referred to the senate a decree of banish- ment would be passed, whereas without such reference Catiline may go into voluntary exile. The real reason for his refusal, however, doubtless was that the senate had no right to pass such a decree.
